(2) Effective Velocity Dispersion\sigma_{\rm eff,avg} = 11.7{\rm km/s}\; P_4^{0.12} = 13.4{\rm km/s}\;n_0^{0.16} In either case, we can first solve the cubic equation for a constant $\sigma_{\rm eff}$ to get $H_{\rm gas}$ and $P_{\rm tot}=W_{\rm tot}$. For the non-constant case, we then update $\sigma_{\rm eff}$ based on the new $P_{\rm tot}$ and then solve for $H_{\rm gas}$ and $P_{\rm tot}$ again. We iteratively solve until $H_{\rm gas}$ is converged.

The numerically calibrated total feedback yield from the TIGRESS-classic suite (

